FAQs
What are the benefits of study in Canada?

Studying in Canada offers access to high-quality education, affordable tuition fees, a multicultural environment, and excellent work opportunities.

How can Qadri-International help with my application process

Qadri-International provides personalized guidance, university selection assistance, comprehensive application support, and visa and immigration guidance.

Are there work opportunities for international students in Canada?

Yes, international students can work part-time while studying and participate in the Post-Graduation Work Permit Program (PGWPP) after graduation.

What are the living costs for students in Canada?

Living costs vary depending on the city and lifestyle, but students can manage expenses through part-time work and scholarships.

How do I choose the right university in Canada?

Qadri-International helps you choose the right university by considering your academic profile, career goals, and personal preferences.
